# Digital Twin — worktree rules

Global patterns: `agent-worktrees` skill · `22-parallel-agents.mdc`. Repo scripts: `scripts/agent-worktree.sh`, `scripts/agent-worktree-best-of-n.sh`.

## Do not use worktrees for

- Editing `docker-compose.dev.yml` or shared smoke scripts
- Integration debugging (Debezium, Flink, Redis, cross-service chains)
- Anything requiring `./scripts/smoke-test.sh` or `./scripts/smoke-test-phase2.sh` from the child

Parent runs Compose + smoke from **this repo's main root** only.

## Track scopes (non-overlapping)

| Track | May edit | Must not |
|-------|----------|----------|
| `backend` | `services/*`, `jobs/*` | `apps/*`, Compose, smoke scripts |
| `frontend` | `apps/*` | `services/*`, Compose, smoke scripts |
| `docs` | `docs/`, `policies/`, eval docs | Service code unless explicit |
| `experiment` | Confirm with parent | Compose without port coordination |

## Parent checklist

Use `/parallel-parent` or [docs/handoff-parallel-parent.md](../docs/handoff-parallel-parent.md):

1. `./scripts/agent-worktree-best-of-n.sh compare --prefix <id>` (if best-of-N)
2. `./scripts/check-worktree-scope.sh --branch <branch> --strict`
3. Review diff; merge winner onto integration branch
4. `./scripts/verify-worktree-merge.sh <branch> --rebuild` then `--rebuild --with-smoke` on main root
5. `./scripts/agent-worktree.sh remove` or `agent-worktree-best-of-n.sh remove`

## False smoke risk

Running `./scripts/smoke-test*.sh` from a worktree cwd hits the **main Docker stack**, not unmerged code — guard-shell blocks this. Parent must rebuild services on main root before smoke.

## Hygiene

```bash
./scripts/check-agent-worktrees.sh
```

Stale batches under `.worktrees/` confuse future agents — remove after merge.
